item.description:
 Background My cluster has two nodes:
​ node_1: Public IP, small disk space;
​ node_2: Private IP, large disk space;
So, I need to download files on node_1 and move all of them to node_2 at intervals.
Method  After enough large files are downloaded, I just move them to node_2;
 Copy files&rsquo; attributes to node_1
   cp -r --attributes-only &lt;node_1_directory&gt; &lt;ndoe_2_directory&gt;   Download again by -nc option on node_1:   wget --no-check-certificate -nc -e robots=off -r -l inf -np -R .html,.tmp -nH --cut-dirs=3 https://ladsweb.modaps.eosdis.nasa.gov/archive/orders/501249136/ --header &quot;Authorization: Bearer &lt;APP_KEY&gt;&quot; -P ./   Delete empty fiels:   find . -type f -empty -delete   Repeat 1-4&hellip;&hellip;
